  "title": "Multiple Neurosis",
  "description": "Karin Fekko weaves tales of hilarity and tragedy through 17 years of keeping her MS a secret while partying, dating, and trying to land her dream job. This show is about invisible disability, internalized ableism, and big-time denial. Can we laugh about it? Karin thinks so. Join her as she marks 20 years since her MS diagnosis.",
  "credits": "<strong>Website/Socials</strong>: @karinfekko",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "Multiple Neurosis is a storytelling show about a disease I have called Multiple Sclerosis. I tell stories about having a disability that is invisible. For example, when I was blind in one eye, other people did not notice. I talk about hiding my disability for 17 years, when going to parties, going on dates, and going to work. The show is about me trying to feel ok about having a disability, and not being ashamed. I have had Multiple Sclerosis for 20 years, and I finally tell people about it, instead of hiding it. I balance the serious parts of the show with fun and comedy.",
